<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,474,643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,582,607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="320">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition compounded from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[1186,1271,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="320">chrysos</emphasis>
meaning gold and 
<emphasis box="[198,257,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="320">soma</emphasis>
meaning body, in reference to the insect’s extensive golden yellow markings.
</paragraph>
