<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1268,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Abdomen long and fairly robust; S 
<number box="[609,621,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="1.0">1</number>
, S 
<number box="[652,667,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="2.0">2</number>
tergites entirely bright yellow; remainder dark dorsally with wide yellow basal spot on S 
<number box="[404,419,1305,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="3.0">3</number>
, paired, very small lateral spots on S 
<number box="[831,877,1305,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
; yellowish, thin, transverse apical bands on S 
<number box="[1386,1431,1305,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
; laterally S 
<number box="[265,322,1341,1365]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10</number>
with lower parts yellowish, the sinuous margin becoming thinner posteriorly so at S 
<number box="[1274,1303,1341,1365]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="10.0">10</number>
pale colour confined to venter; apical half of dorsum of S 
<number box="[657,686,1377,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="10.0">10</number>
strongly raised to form a pyramid with faint pale marks along crest and posterior prominence. Appendages as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[758,831,1413,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1177,1199]" captionTargetBox="[242,1344,201,1147]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[234,1353,193,1155]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lateral view male appendages: (a) P. chrysosoma holotype ♂; (b) P. marijanmatoki holotype ♂; (c) P. tydecksjuerging holotype ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270695/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Figs 
<number box="[816,831,1413,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
a, 
<number box="[860,875,1413,1438]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="5.0">5</number>
a,b,c. Upper branch of cercus in profile thin and strongly curved downwards, black; lower branch robust, about half length of upper, terminating in a thin sharp upwardly curved spine, basally brownish with tip dark. Paraproct in profile with very broad, short, yellowish base and long, thin, dark spine arising from upper third nearly reaching level of cercus tip; in ventral view paraprocts (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,203,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Caudal, dorsal and ventral views of male appendages for, respectively: P. chrysosoma holotype ♂ (a, b, c); P. marijanmatoki holotype ♂ (d, e, f); P. tydecksjuerging holotype ♂ (g, h, i)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,229,1557,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
c) roughly triangular with a small inner shoulder. Anal plate, best seen in caudal view (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1326,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,203,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Caudal, dorsal and ventral views of male appendages for, respectively: P. chrysosoma holotype ♂ (a, b, c); P. marijanmatoki holotype ♂ (d, e, f); P. tydecksjuerging holotype ♂ (g, h, i)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270696/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Fig. 
<number box="[1312,1326,1557,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a), broad, divergent with two distinct arms, dark brown; in ventral view tips visible beyond margins of paraprocts. Measurements (mm): hindwing 
<number box="[511,562,1629,1654]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="26.5">26.5</number>
, abdomen + appendages 
<number box="[844,877,1629,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="42.0">42</number>
.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1268,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,531,1664,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Variation in male 
<typeStatus box="[416,525,1664,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">paratype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Slightly larger than 
<typeStatus box="[764,866,1664,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">holotype</typeStatus>
: Hindwing 
<quantity box="[998,1101,1664,1689]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" unit="mm" value="28.5">28.5 mm</quantity>
, abdomen + appendages 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" unit="mm" value="44.5">44.5 mm</quantity>
; forewings Px 15, 15; hindwings Px 14, 15; yellow and orange markings on head slightly reduced; pale marking on ventral parts of abdominal S 
<number box="[599,656,1737,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10</number>
clearly reduced with venter of S 
<number box="[1018,1032,1737,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="9.0">9</number>
besmirched; anal plate more clearly triangular, not incised along lateral margin and less so posteriorly than in 
<typeStatus box="[995,1096,1773,1798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">holotype</typeStatus>
; paler in colour. 
<figureCitation box="[1290,1357,1773,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1659,1681]" captionText="FIGURE 7. (a) P. chrysosoma paratype ♂ in life; (b) same, detail of head, anterior view." pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Fig. 
<number box="[1343,1357,1774,1797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
shows this individual in life.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1268,2014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,576,1845,1870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[375,483,1845,1870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">paratype</typeStatus>
female.
</emphasis>
Head: Labium marked as in male, ground colour slightly darker. Mandibles, labrum, and entire face marked as in male but yellow replaced by dark orange-tinged brown, with deep orange highlights at various sutures; paler area along eye margin from genae to level of median ocellus tending to greenish. Remainder of head matt black except for two well-separated, small, brownish orange spots on hind margin near inner corner of postoccipital lobes.
</paragraph>
