<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1512,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">
Thorax: Prothorax (
<figureCitation box="[427,497,1512,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1219,1241]" captionTargetBox="[239,1349,193,1195]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[234,1353,193,1197]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal view of prothorax: (a) P. chrysosoma holotype ♂; (b) P. chrysosoma paratype ♀; (c) P. marijanmatoki holotype ♂; (d) P. marijanmatoki paratype ♀; (e) P. tydecksjuerging holotype ♂; (f) P. tydecksjuerging paratype ♀." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270693/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">
Fig. 
<number box="[483,497,1512,1537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b) generally as in male but black marking less well defined and more extensive; posterior lobe in dorsal view with hind margin centrally excavated to about half its depth, the excavation including two short, median, finger-like processes separated by a deeper narrow excavation; lateral lobes only slightly produced inwards. Synthorax marked as in male with colours slightly less brilliant and dark areas blending less distinctly. Wings as in male; forewings Px 15, 15; hindwings Px 14, 14.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1512,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">
Abdomen long and robust; S 
<number box="[531,543,1693,1717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="1.0">1</number>
, S 
<number box="[572,587,1693,1717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="2.0">2</number>
tergites entirely bright yellow as in male but some infuscation apically on S 
<number box="[167,183,1728,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="2.0">2</number>
; S 
<number box="[211,268,1728,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10</number>
marked as in male but pale colour less extensive than 
<typeStatus box="[896,998,1728,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">holotype</typeStatus>
; extensive drab orange marking on S 
<number box="[1422,1436,1728,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="8.0">8</number>
and S 
<number box="[215,229,1765,1789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="9.0">9</number>
and sides of valvae mainly straw-yellow edged with black. Cerci black, slightly longer than S 
<number box="[1302,1331,1765,1789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="10.0">10</number>
along its dorsal margin; paraproct shallow, dark. Anal plate shaped as in male but smaller, smoothly incised along lateral margins but posterior margin only slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[740,807,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[269,1316,203,1376]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[269,1317,193,1393]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view female terminalia showing anal plate: (a) P. chrysosoma; (c) P. marijanmatoki; (e) P. tydecksjuerging. Lateral view of female ovipositor: (b) P. chrysosoma; (d) P. marijanmatoki; (f) P. tydecksjuerging." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270697/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">
Fig. 
<number box="[792,807,1836,1861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Ovipositor well developed with very fine teeth along ventral margin; tip of valves surpassing hind margin of S 
<number box="[788,817,1872,1896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="10.0">10</number>
and stylus extending beyond tip of cercus (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1371,1872,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1415,1437]" captionTargetBox="[269,1316,203,1376]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[269,1317,193,1393]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view female terminalia showing anal plate: (a) P. chrysosoma; (c) P. marijanmatoki; (e) P. tydecksjuerging. Lateral view of female ovipositor: (b) P. chrysosoma; (d) P. marijanmatoki; (f) P. tydecksjuerging." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270697/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="325">
Fig. 
<number box="[1356,1371,1872,1897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="325" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
